y of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When David John VYCHAN was born about 1465, in Glamorgan, Wales, his father, Roger Vaughan, was 32 and his mother, Mrs. Roger Vaughan, was 21. He married Elizabeth verch Griffith about 1490, in Glamorgan, Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1495, at the age of 32."},"et":{"about 1465–about 1495":"umbes 1465–umbes 1495","1465–1495":"1465–1495","1470–1565":"1470–1565","1495–1522":"1495–1522","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1446–Female":"1446–Surnud","1446":"1446","1435":"1435","about 1490":"umbes 1490","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1565":"1565","1465":"1465","1495":"1495","about 1465":"umbes 1465","1470":"1470","about 1495":"umbes 1495","<1485>":"1485","Porthamel, Anglesey, Wales":"Porthamel, Anglesey, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1465–about 1495":"noin 1465–noin 1495","1465–1495":"1465–1495","1470–1565":"1470–1565","1495–1522":"1495–1522","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1446–Female":"1446–Kuollut","1446":"1446","1435":"1435","about 1490":"noin 1490","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1565":"1565","1465":"1465","1495":"1495","about 1465":"noin 1465","1470":"1470","about 1495":"noin 1495","<1485>":"1485","Porthamel, Anglesey, Wales":"Porthamel, Anglesey, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1465–about 1495":"environ 1465–environ 1495","1465–1495":"1465–1495","1470–1565":"1470–1565","1